{"title_page": "Dark Horse (Katy Perry song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2013 single by Katy Perry featuring Juicy J}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Dark Horse\n| cover      = DarkHorseCover.png\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Katy Perry]] featuring [[Juicy J]]\n| album      = [[Prism (Katy Perry album)|Prism]]\n| released   = December 17, 2013\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     = {{ubl|Playback Recording Studios|([[Santa Barbara, California]])|[[MXM Studios]]| ([[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]])|Luke's in the Boo|([[Malibu, California]])|Secret Garden Studios|([[Montecito, California]])}}\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist||[[Trap music|Trap]]|[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]|[[Electropop|electropop]]}}<!-- Sourced in the \"Composition\" section -->\n| length     = 3:35\n| label      = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|Katy Perry|[[Juicy J|Jordan Houston]]|[[Dr. Luke|Lukasz Gottwald]]|[[Sarah Hudson (singer)|Sarah Hudson]]|[[Max Martin]]|[[Cirkut (record producer)|Henry Walter]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[Dr. Luke]]|Max Martin|[[Cirkut (record producer)|Cirkut]]}}\n| chronology = [[Katy Perry]]\n| prev_title = [[Unconditionally]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Birthday (Katy Perry song)|Birthday]]\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Juicy J]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Lolly (song)|Lolly]]\n | prev_year  = 2013\n | title      = Dark Horse\n | year       = 2013\n | next_title = [[Shell Shocked (song)|Shell Shocked]]\n | next_year  = 2014\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|0KSOMA3QBU0|\"Dark Horse\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Dark Horse'''\" is a song by American singer [[Katy Perry]] featuring rapper [[Juicy J]]. It was originally released on September 17, 2013, by [[Capitol Records]] as the first promotional single from Perry's fourth [[studio album]], ''[[Prism (Katy Perry album)|Prism]]'' (2013). Three months later, it was released as the third official single on December 17. Both artists co-wrote the song with its producers, [[Max Martin]], [[Cirkut (record producer)|Cirkut]], and [[Dr. Luke]], alongside [[Sarah Hudson (singer)|Sarah Hudson]]. It was conceived by Perry and Hudson during a writing session in Perry's hometown of [[Santa Barbara, California]], and Juicy J was later commissioned for a verse on the song.\n\n\"Dark Horse\" combines the genres of [[Pop music|pop]], [[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]], [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] and [[Electropop|electropop]], replicating what has been described as a \"[[Southern rap]]-[[techno]] mashup\". The track features a minimal production, with a \"seductive\" and \"mature\" tone to Perry's vocals, while Juicy J is featured on the song's intro and [[Rapping|rapped]] [[Bridge (music)|bridge]]. Perry, in interviews, said she wanted the song to have a \"witchy, [[Spell (paranormal)|spell]]-y kind of [[black magic]]-y idea\", so she wrote it from the perspective of a [[witch]] warning a man not to [[falling in love|fall in love]] with her because if he does, she will be his last. The song was part of a competition sponsored by [[Pepsi]] in which fans could vote via [[Twitter]] on whether they would prefer either \"Dark Horse\" or \"[[Walking on Air (Katy Perry song)|Walking on Air]]\" to be released as the first promotional single from ''Prism''. \n\n\"Dark Horse\" was a commercial success, charting at number one in Canada, the [[Netherlands]] and the United States. It also reached the top ten in almost 20 countries including [[New Zealand]], United Kingdom, [[Sweden]] and [[Venezuela]] as well as the Digital Songs chart of ''Billboard'' magazine.<ref name=\"Caulfield\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5855135/beyonce-leads-for-third-week-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart |title=Beyonce Leads for Third Week at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart |first=Keith |last=Caulfield |work=Billboard |date=January 2, 2014 |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104075520/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5855135/beyonce-leads-for-third-week-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart |archivedate=January 4, 2014 }}</ref> ''Billboard'' identified Dark Horse as cementing trap music's place on the charts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2015/6804537/justin-bieber-omi-kygo-lillywood-robin-schulz-mr-probs-tropical-house-hits-2015|title=How Justin Bieber, OMI and More Helped Tropical House Heat Up in 2015|website=Billboard}}</ref> Perry first performed the song live at the 2013 [[iHeartRadio Music Festival]] in [[Las Vegas]] on September 20, 2013. The song's first major television performance was at the [[56th Annual Grammy Awards]] on January 26, 2014.<ref name=\"GrammyPerformance2014\" /> \"Dark Horse\" was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Duo/Group Performance|Best Pop Duo/Group Performance]] at the [[57th Annual Grammy Awards]]. The song has sold 13.2 million units (combined sales and track-equivalent streams), becoming the second best-selling song worldwide for 2014. As of 2019, it is one of the best selling songs in digital history. <ref name=\"Ifpi2015\">{{cite web|title=IFPI publishes Digital Music Report 2015 |url=http://www.ifpi.org/news/Global-digital-music-revenues-match-physical-format-sales-for-first-time |publisher=International Federation of the Phonographic Industry |date=14 April 2015 |accessdate=15 April 2015 |page=12 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414194629/http://www.ifpi.org/news/Global-digital-music-revenues-match-physical-format-sales-for-first-time |archivedate=April 14, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, [[Flame (rapper)|Flame]], a [[Christian hip hop|Christian rap]] artist, filed a copyright infringement lawsuit against Perry and the other songwriters, claiming that \"Dark Horse\" copied from his 2008 song \"Joyful Noise\". On July 29, 2019, a federal jury ruled in favor of Flame and the co-plaintiffs Da' T.R.U.T.H. and  Chike Ojukwu. The jury ordered Perry, her collaborators, and associated labels to pay $2.78 million in damages. Of this, Perry was ordered to pay $550,000. However, in part due to a similar judgement that found [[Led Zeppelin]]'s \"[[Stairway to Heaven]]\" clear of copyright infringement in the [[United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit|Ninth Circuit]], the jury award was vacated on appeal in March 2020.\n\n==Production and release==\nInspired by the 1996 film ''[[The Craft (film)|The Craft]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5763220/katy-perry-reveals-prism-influences-adds-stripped-down |title=Katy Perry Reveals 'Prism' Influences, Adds Stripped-Down Performances at Album Release Event |author=Rutherford, Kevin |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=February 11, 2014 |date=October 22, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027052306/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5763220/katy-perry-reveals-prism-influences-adds-stripped-down |archivedate=October 27, 2013 }}</ref> Perry and singer-songwriter Sarah Hudson wrote the first version of \"Dark Horse\" in Perry's hometown of [[Santa Barbara, California]].<ref name=\"MTV1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1713269/katy-perry-dark-horse-prism.jhtml |title=Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Is A 'Warning' |first=Christina |last=Garibaldi |publisher=[[MTV News]] |date=August 29, 2013 |accessdate=December 8, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203083356/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1713269/katy-perry-dark-horse-prism.jhtml |archivedate=December 3, 2013 }}</ref> Perry described the song as a \"[[wiktionary:juxtaposition|juxtaposition]]\", as it mixed her, a [[pop music]] artist, with an \"urban kind of [[hip-hop]]-flavored background soundtrack\"; and its lyrics as \"witchy and dark\", written from the perspective of \"a witch warning [a] man to not fall in love with [her]\", and if so, she would be his last. Perry then asked producer [[Dr. Luke]] to contact one of his [[Kemosabe Records]] artists, American rapper [[Juicy J]], for a guest verse. Juicy J complimented Perry as having a \"very professional\" work ethic and being substantially involved in the song's development. He said: \"My verse I did on that song, she was singing it. She's really a genius, she was by the mixing board and telling the guy what to take in and take out. She's really hands-on with her music, she knows music.\"<ref name=\"Collab\">{{cite web |url=http://news.mtv.ca/news/music/katy-perrys-dark-horse-shows-off-her-genius-juicy-j-says/ |title=Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Shows Off Her 'Genius,' Juicy J Says |first=Rob |last=Markman |publisher=MTV News. Viacom |date=September 10, 2013 |accessdate=September 22, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006084633/http://news.mtv.ca/news/music/katy-perrys-dark-horse-shows-off-her-genius-juicy-j-says/ |archivedate=October 6, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n\"Dark Horse\" was recorded and engineered at Luke's in the Boo in [[Malibu, California|Malibu]], [[Conway Recording Studios]] in [[Hollywood]], Playback Recording Studios in Santa Barbara, California, and Secret Garden Studios in [[Montecito, California|Montecito]], as well as [[MXM Studios]] in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. It was engineered by Peter Carlsson, Mike \"Crazy Mike\" Foster, Clint Gibbs, Sam Holland, and Michael Ilbert. They were assisted by Eric Eylands, Rachael Findlen, Justin Fox, Elliot Lanam, and Cory Bice. It was mixed by Serban Ghenea, while John Hanes served as the engineer for mix. All instrumentation and programming was done by Dr. Luke, Max Martin, and Cirkut.<ref name=\"Notes\">{{cite AV media notes|others=Katy Perry|title=[[Prism (Katy Perry album)|Prism]]|year=2013|type= inlay cover |publisher= [[Capitol Records]]|page=6}}</ref>\n\nIn a press release on August 20, 2013, [[Pepsi]] announced a partnership with Perry to promote her fourth studio album ''Prism'': a social \"[[Twitter|tweet]]-to-unlock\" voting program, encouraging fans to tweet the hashtag #KATYNOW in exchange for song titles and lyrics. The chosen tracks for the campaign were \"Walking on Air\" and \"Dark Horse\". After the samples were revealed, fans could vote for which one they wanted to have an early release on digital retailers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pepsi And MTV Team Up With Global Superstar Katy Perry For Special Finale Performance From Undisclosed Location In Brooklyn During The 2013 'MTV Video Music Awards' |url=http://www.pepsico.com/PressRelease/Pepsi-And-MTV-Team-Up-With-Global-Superstar-Katy-Perry-For-Special-Finale-Perfor08202013.html |publisher=[[PepsiCo]] |accessdate=December 17, 2013 |date=August 20, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131216184104/http://www.pepsico.com/PressRelease/Pepsi-And-MTV-Team-Up-With-Global-Superstar-Katy-Perry-For-Special-Finale-Perfor08202013.html |archivedate=December 16, 2013 }}</ref> The winner was \"Dark Horse\", which was released on September 17, 2013 on the [[iTunes Store]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Lee, Christina |title=Katy Perry Will Drop 'Dark Horse' (Featuring Juicy J) As Her Next 'Prism' Single |url=http://www.idolator.com/7480598/katy-perry-next-prism-single-dark-horse-juicy-j |publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]. [[SpinMedia]]. |accessdate=January 10, 2014 |date=August 26, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20131203204732/http://www.idolator.com/7480598/katy-perry-next-prism-single-dark-horse-juicy-j |archivedate=December 3, 2013 }}</ref> Due to its commercial success, it was sent to [[Contemporary hit radio|contemporary hit]] and [[Rhythmic contemporary|rhythmic]] radio stations on December 17, 2013 as ''Prism''{{'}}s third official single.<ref name=\"Trust\" /><ref name=\"plaympe\">{{cite web|url=http://daily.plaympe.com/katy-perry-feat-juicy-j-dark-horse-2/ |title=Katy Perry feat. Juicy J \u2013 Dark Horse |publisher=Play MPE. Destiny Media Technologies |date=December 17, 2013 |accessdate=December 18, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219063251/http://daily.plaympe.com/katy-perry-feat-juicy-j-dark-horse-2/ |archivedate=December 19, 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Dark Horse\" is a [[pop music|pop]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liveabout.com/review-katy-perry-dark-horse-3243926|title=Review of Katy Perry's \"Dark Horse\"|website=LiveAbout}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolvermag.com/music/see-hardcore-punk-act-war-womens-raucous-cover-katy-perrys-dark-horse|title=See Hardcore Punk Act War On Women's Raucous Cover of Katy Perry's \"Dark Horse\"|date=November 7, 2018|website=Revolver}}</ref>, [[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]<ref name=\"Trap\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5687099/katy-perrys-prism-album-preview-10-things-you-need-to-know |title=Katy Perry's 'Prism' Album Preview: 10 Things You Need To Know |first=Jason |last=Lipshutz |work=Billboard |date=September 6, 2013 |accessdate=September 22, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304072407/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5687099/katy-perrys-prism-album-preview-10-things-you-need-to-know |archivedate=March 4, 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"Trap1\">{{cite magazine|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2013/09/listen-katy-perry-goes-trap-with-juicy-j-on-dark-horse/ |title=Listen: Katy Perry goes trap with Juicy J on \"Dark Horse\" |magazine=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=September 17, 2013 |accessdate=September 22, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921151619/http://consequenceofsound.net/2013/09/listen-katy-perry-goes-trap-with-juicy-j-on-dark-horse/ |archivedate=September 21, 2013 }}</ref>, [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]<ref name=\"Billboard2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5687099/katy-perrys-prism-album-preview-10-things-you-need-to-know |title=Katy Perry's 'Prism' Album Preview: 10 Things You Need To Know |first=Jason |last=Lipshutz |work=Billboard |date=September 6, 2013 |accessdate=September 6, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304072407/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5687099/katy-perrys-prism-album-preview-10-things-you-need-to-know |archivedate=March 4, 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"Billboard3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5695549/miley-cyrus-britney-spears-katy-perry-whose-new-song-is-best |title=Miley Cyrus, Britney Spears, Katy Perry: Whose New Song Is Best? |work=Billboard |date=September 17, 2013 |accessdate=September 22, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922051500/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5695549/miley-cyrus-britney-spears-katy-perry-whose-new-song-is-best |archivedate=September 22, 2013 }}</ref> and [[electropop|pop electro]] song.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/reviews-record-release-rundown-latest-katy-perry-best/story?id=20687045|title=Reviews: Latest from Katy Perry, Best Coast and Van Morrison|last=Raible|first=Allan|publisher=[[ABC News]]|date=21 October 2013|accessdate=13 September 2019}}</ref> which is styled in \"[[Southern rap]]-[[techno]] mashup\",<ref name=\"Denver\">{{cite web|url=http://www.denverpost.com/ci_24032311/katy-perry-previews-new-album-prism-at-nyc |title=Katy Perry Previews New Album 'Prism' at NYC Event |first=Mesfin |last=Fedaku |work=[[The Denver Post]] |date=September 6, 2013 |accessdate=September 6, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908120125/http://www.denverpost.com/ci_24032311/katy-perry-previews-new-album-prism-at-nyc |archivedate=September 8, 2013 }}</ref> and has a length of three minutes and thirty-five seconds.<ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/prism-deluxe-version/id690928033 |title=Katy Perry \u2014 \"Prism\" |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] |date=September 17, 2013 |accessdate=September 17, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012053806/https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/prism-deluxe-version/id690928033 |archivedate=October 12, 2013 }}</ref> Musically, the verses are built around icy rhythms and [[chopped and screwed]] vocal samples, while the chorus' feature Perry singing into a gradual [[crescendo]].<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5695532/katy-perry-teams-with-juicy-j-on-dark-horse-hear-the-new-track |title=Katy Perry Teams With Juicy J on 'Dark Horse': Hear The New Track |first=Jason |last=Lipshutz |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=September 17, 2013 |accessdate=September 22, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921084910/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5695532/katy-perry-teams-with-juicy-j-on-dark-horse-hear-the-new-track |archivedate=September 21, 2013 }}</ref> The song contains a grimy, \"incredibly simplistic\" production.<ref name=\"Trap\" /> According to Kathy Iandoli of [[MSN Entertainment]], \"Dark Horse\" contains a mixture of elements from \"trippy [[Pop music|pop]]\", [[Electronic dance music|EDM]], and [[dubstep]].<ref name=\"MSN\">{{cite web |url=http://social.entertainment.msn.com/music/blogs/post--katy-perry-enlists-juicy-j-for-her-fan-voted-next-single-dark-horse |title=Katy Perry enlists Juicy J for her fan-voted next single 'Dark Horse' |first=Kathy |last=Iandoli |work=[[MSN Entertainment]] |publisher=[[Microsoft]] |date=September 17, 2013 |accessdate=December 8, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226203203/http://social.entertainment.msn.com/music/blogs/post--katy-perry-enlists-juicy-j-for-her-fan-voted-next-single-dark-horse |archivedate=December 26, 2013 }}</ref> According to the sheet music published at Musicnotes.com, \"Dark Horse\" is written in the key of [[B-flat minor|B{{music|flat}} minor]].  It follows a chord progression of G{{music|flat}} \u2013 D{{music|flat}} \u2013 B{{music|flat}}m \u2013 B{{music|flat}}m/A{{music|flat}}, and the vocals range from the low note of [[B\u266d (musical note)|B{{music|flat}}<sub>3</sub>]] to the high note of [[D\u266d (musical note)|D{{music|flat}}<sub>5</sub>]]. \"Dark Horse\" has a tempo of 132 beats per minute in half-time style typical of trap music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0125299 |title=Unsupported Browser or Operating System |publisher=Musicnotes.com |accessdate=March 4, 2014|date=September 25, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nA writer for the ''[[Winnipeg Free Press]]'' described the song as \"brooding, borderline sleazy trap-pop excursion that comes across like a stripped-down version of \"[[E.T. (song)|E.T.]]\" mixed with \"[[Grindin']]\" by [[The Clipse]],\" before going on to call it unexpected, unconventional, and unstoppable.<ref name=\"Winnipeg\">{{cite news|url=http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/arts-and-life/entertainment/music/new-music-225307012.html |title=New music |newspaper=[[Winnipeg Free Press]] |publisher=Bob Cox |date=September 26, 2013 |accessdate=December 11, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003060656/http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/arts-and-life/entertainment/music/new-music-225307012.html |archivedate=October 3, 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[File:Three 6 Mafia.jpg|thumb|200px|left|The critical response to guest vocals from [[Juicy J]] (pictured) was generally negative.]]\nMarc Hogan from ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' called the lyrics a \"clich\u00e9 salad\" but believed that the song had potential to become a hit due to its \"soaring hooks\" and \"sleekly sculpted production\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry and Juicy J's Trap-Minded 'Dark Horse' Easily Beats the Spread |url=https://www.spin.com/2013/09/katy-perry-juicy-j-dark-horse-prism-stream/ |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |accessdate=January 9, 2014 |date=September 17, 2013 |author=Hogan, Marc |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125112500/https://www.spin.com/2013/09/katy-perry-juicy-j-dark-horse-prism-stream/ |archivedate=January 25, 2014 }}</ref> Reviewing the song for ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', Jason Lipshutz said that by exploring trap-influenced music, Perry \"score[d]\" and \"slay[ed]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry's 'PRISM': Track-By-Track Review |author=Lipshutz, Jason |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/5763162/katy-perrys-prism-track-by-track-review |work=Billboard |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 21, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219095623/http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/5763162/katy-perrys-prism-track-by-track-review |archivedate=February 19, 2014 }}</ref> [[Digital Spy]]'s Robert Copsey questioned the decision to not have a proper chorus in \"Dark Horse\" and the inclusion of [[Juicy J]], though he praised the \"sleazy\" beat and \"sultry\" vocals from Katy Perry. He gave the track a rating of four stars out of five.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/review/a544861/katy-perry-dark-horse-review-a-strangely-addictive-curveball.html |title=Katy Perry: 'Dark Horse' review: 'A strangely addictive curveball' |date=January 17, 2014 |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |author=Copsey, Robert |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201113827/http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/review/a544861/katy-perry-dark-horse-review-a-strangely-addictive-curveball.html |archivedate=February 1, 2014 }}</ref> Contributor Dylan Mial of [[Blogcritics]] said the \"[[wiktionary:juxtaposition|juxtaposition]]\" of Perry's vocals and Juicy J's rap brought \"the ingredients for a perfect musical storm\" and favored Perry for the \"uniqueness\" of the single.<ref name=\"blogcritics\">{{cite magazine|title=Music Review: Katy Perry \u2013 \"Dark Horse\" Single|date=October 1, 2013|accessdate=February 10, 2014|url=http://blogcritics.org/music-review-katy-perry-dark-horse-single/|magazine=[[Blogcritics]]|author=Mial, Dylan}}</ref>\n\nKeith Murphy from ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]'' called the track \"infectiously sexy\",<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=September 18, 2013 |title=Review: Katy Perry Visits The Trap (With Juicy J) On 'Dark Horse' |url=http://www.vibe.com/article/review-katy-perry-visits-trap-juicy-j-dark-horse |author=Murphy, Keith |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217170746/http://www.vibe.com/article/review-katy-perry-visits-trap-juicy-j-dark-horse |archivedate=February 17, 2014 }}</ref> while John Walker from MTV was similarly positive about the song, though he wrote that Juicy's verse was \"phoned-in\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Walker |first=John |publisher=[[MTV]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 22, 2013 |title=Katy Perry's 'Prism': A Track-By-Track Review..... In Cat GIFs! |url=http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2013/10/22/katy-perry-prism-review-cat-gifs/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140206163508/http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2013/10/22/katy-perry-prism-review-cat-gifs |archivedate=February 6, 2014 }}</ref> Sal Cinquemani of ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' likened the song to avant-garde band [[Art of Noise]]'s song \"Moments In Love\" and called it a \"continuation\" of \"[[E.T. (song)|E.T.]]\", and further labelled it as a \"standout\" from ''Prism''.<ref>{{cite web|work=Slant |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 17, 2013 |author=Cinquemani, Sal |title=Katy Perry \u2014 Prism |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-prism |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125115444/http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-prism |archivedate=January 25, 2014 }}</ref> While she did not give her opinion of the song as a whole, Helen Brown from the publication ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' criticized Juicy J for his \"daft\" rap.<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite news|title=Katy Perry, Prism, review |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/rockandpopreviews/10386191/Katy-Perry-Prism-review.html |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 17, 2013 |author=Brown, Helen |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140126035023/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/rockandpopreviews/10386191/Katy-Perry-Prism-review.html |archivedate=January 26, 2014 }}</ref> For [[AbsolutePunk]], Craig Manning classified \"Dark Horse\" as ''Prism''{{'}}s worst song, while also panning the rapper's contribution.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[AbsolutePunk]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 28, 2013 |title=Katy Perry - Prism |url=http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=3502811 |author=Manning, Craig |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20140210213748/http://www.absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=3502811 |archivedate=February 10, 2014 }}</ref> Marah Eakin from ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' was not entirely critical of the song, though she noted that it was not among \"Perry's best\".<ref>{{cite web|work=[[The A.V. Club]] |publisher=[[The Onion]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 22, 2013 |author=Eakin, Marah |title=Katy Perry: Prism |url=https://www.avclub.com/review/katy-perry-iprismi-104560 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140218014302/http://www.avclub.com/review/katy-perry-iprismi-104560 |archivedate=February 18, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n[[Consequence of Sound]]'s Chris Bosman had a mixed response\u2014while he praised the song for feeling \"vital\" and \"forward-moving\", he criticized the guest vocals and nonetheless deemed the trap influence \"trap for soccer moms\".<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Consequence of Sound]] |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 21, 2013 |title=Album Review: Katy Perry \u2014 Prism |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2013/10/album-review-katy-perry-prism/ |author=Bosman, Chris |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140210155350/http://consequenceofsound.net/2013/10/album-review-katy-perry-prism/ |archivedate=February 10, 2014 }}</ref> Writing for [[ABC News]], Mesfin Fekadu commented that \"her team fare[d] better\" in the song and observed that the \"Southern hip-hop and electronic flavors\" present on it were factors that made it \"work\".<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ABC News]]. [[American Broadcasting Company]]. |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |author=Fekadu, Mesfin |title=Music Review: Katy Perry Plays It Safe on 'Prism' |date=October 21, 2013 |url=http://abcnews.go.com/m/story?id=20636044 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125180258/http://abcnews.go.com/m/story?id=20636044 |archivedate=January 25, 2014 }}</ref> Pop music website [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'s Sam Lansky opined that the \"weird trap-lite\" of the song \"never quite [[wiktionary:coalesce|coalesces]]\".<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]. [[Spin Media]]. |accessdate=February 10, 2014 |date=October 22, 2013 |title=Katy Perry's 'Prism': Album Review |url=http://www.idolator.com/7489676/katy-perry-prism-review |author=Lansky, Sam |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20131022193841/http://www.idolator.com/7489676/katy-perry-prism-review |archivedate=October 22, 2013 }}</ref> The song was nominated for [[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Song|Best Song]] at the [[2014 MTV Europe Music Awards]], though lost to [[Ariana Grande]]'s \"[[Problem (Ariana Grande song)|Problem]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 MTV EMAs: The Complete Winners List |url=http://www.etonline.com/awards/153667_2014_mtv_emas_the_complete_winners_list/ |publisher=Entertainment Tonight |accessdate=December 6, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141128094657/http://www.etonline.com/awards/153667_2014_mtv_emas_the_complete_winners_list/ |archivedate=November 28, 2014 }}</ref> It has been nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Duo/Group Performance|Best Pop Duo/Group Performance]] at the [[57th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Moraski |first1=Lauren |title=Grammy Awards 2015 nominations announced |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/grammy-awards-2015-nominations-announced/ |accessdate=December 6, 2014 |publisher=CBS News |date=December 5, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205170353/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/grammy-awards-2015-nominations-announced/ |archivedate=December 5, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Awards\n! Category\n! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"11\"| 2014\n|[[MuchMusic Video Awards]]\n|[[MuchMusic Video Award for Best International Artist Video|Best International Artist Video]]\n|rowspan=4 {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[2014 Premios Juventud|Premios Juventud]]\n|Favorite Hit\n|-\n|[[2014 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[2014 Teen Choice Awards#Choice Music|Choice Music: Single by a Female Artist]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[2014 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Collaboration|Best Collaboration]]\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Female Video|Best Female Video]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[2014 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]]\n|[[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Song|Best Song]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Video|Best Video]]\n|rowspan=2 {{won}}\n|-\n|[[American Music Awards of 2014|American Music Awards]]\n|[[American Music Award for Single of the Year|Single of the Year]]\n|-\n|MP3 Music Awards\n|Radio/Charts/Downloads Award\n|rowspan=8 {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Los Premios 40 Principales 2014|Los Premios 40 Principales]]\n| Best International Video\t\n|-\n| [[NRJ Music Awards]]\n| Video of the Year\t\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|2015\n|[[57th Annual Grammy Awards|Grammy Awards]]\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Pop Duo/Group Performance|Best Pop Duo/Group Performance]]\n|-\n|[[ADG Excellence in Production Design Award]]\n|Short Format: Web Series, Music Video or Commercial\n|-\n|[[Myx Music Award]]s\n|[[Myx Music Award for Favorite International Video|Favorite International Video]]\n|-\n|[[2015 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|Favorite Song Of The Year\n|-\n|[[iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Best Collaboration\n|-\n|}\n\n==Chart performance==\n===North America===\nOn the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the song debuted at number seventeen on the week ending October 5, 2013. It also debuted at number four on the [[Hot Digital Songs]] chart with 194,000 downloads.<ref name=\"Billboard4\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5733088/miley-cyrus-wrecking-ball-spends-second-week-atop-hot-100?chartDate=2013-10-05order=gainer&order=gainer |title=Miley Cyrus' 'Wrecking Ball' Spends Second Week Atop Hot 100 |journal=Billboard |accessdate=September 25, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140513210217/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5733088/miley-cyrus-wrecking-ball-spends-second-week-atop-hot-100?chartDate=2013-10-05order%3Dgainer&order=gainer |archivedate=May 13, 2014 }}</ref> In response to the unexpected success of \"Dark Horse\", Capitol Records executive VP [[Greg Thompson (music executive)|Greg Thompson]] stated: \"Katy's well aware of [the success of] 'Dark Horse'\" and \"It might be the next single. We're watching it \u2013 and certainly appreciating the airplay \u2013 while still wanting 'Unconditionally' to have a full run\".<ref name=\"Trust\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5819941/katy-perry-rides-in-on-a-dark-horse-her-aptly-titled-unexpected |title=Katy Perry Rides In On A 'Dark Horse,' Her Aptly Titled, Unexpected Hit (Updated) |journal=Billboard |date=December 9, 2013 |accessdate=December 18, 2013 |last=Trust |first=Gary |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111132238/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5819941/katy-perry-rides-in-on-a-dark-horse-her-aptly-titled-unexpected |archivedate=November 11, 2016 }}</ref> In December, following its success as a promotional single, it was chosen as the third official single from ''Prism''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wass |first=Mike |title=Katy Perry Selects 'Dark Horse' as the Third Single from 'Prism' |url=http://www.idolator.com/7498859/katy-perry-selects-dark-horse-as-the-third-single-from-prism |publisher=Idolator |accessdate=January 9, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20131229194743/http://www.idolator.com/7498859/katy-perry-selects-dark-horse-as-the-third-single-from-prism |archivedate=December 29, 2013 }}</ref> On the week ending January 11, 2014, \"Dark Horse\" sold 285,000 copies (up 158%) ranking at number 7 on [[Hot Digital Songs]] chart. The following week the song rose to number 6 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, and number 4 on the Digital Songs chart selling 229,000 copies. The song became the thirteenth Top 10 song for the singer, and Juicy J's first top 10 on chart.<ref name=\"Caulfield\" /> That same week, the song debuted at number thirty-four on ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs]]. The song also rose to number fifteen on ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Top 40|Pop Songs]], earning greatest gainer honours.<ref name=\"Trust\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5862304/chart-highlights-beyonce-bounds-up-pop-rbhip-hop-charts-with |title=Chart Highlights: Beyonce Bounds Up Pop, R&B/Hip-Hop Charts With 'Drunk In Love,' 'XO' |first=Gary |last=Trust |work=Billboard |date=January 6, 2014 |accessdate=January 8, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109044537/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5862304/chart-highlights-beyonce-bounds-up-pop-rbhip-hop-charts-with |archivedate=January 9, 2014 }}</ref> The following week the song topped the Hot Digital Songs, selling 243,000 copies, and rose to number 4 on the Billboard Hot 100.<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5869748/frozen-chills-for-second-week-at-no-1-on-billboard-200 |title='Frozen' Chills For Second Week At No. 1 On Billboard 200 |first=Keith |last=Caulfield |work=Billboard |date=January 15, 2014 |accessdate=January 15, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140117160222/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5869748/frozen-chills-for-second-week-at-no-1-on-billboard-200 |archivedate=January 17, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5869763/pitbull-kesha-timber-remains-atop-hot-100 |title=Pitbull and Ke$ha's 'Timber' Remains Atop Hot 100 |first=Gary |last=Trust |work=Billboard |date=January 15, 2014 |accessdate=January 15, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140117160229/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5869763/pitbull-kesha-timber-remains-atop-hot-100 |archivedate=January 17, 2014 }}</ref> On the week-ending February 1, 2014 \"Dark Horse\" topped the Hot Digital Song for a second week, selling 261,000 copies and rose to number 2 on the Billboard Hot 100.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5877848/bruce-springsteen-high-hopes-11th-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart |title=Bruce Springsteen Scores 11th No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 |first=Keith |last=Caulfield |work=Billboard |date=January 22, 2014 |accessdate=January 23, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140123070758/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5877848/bruce-springsteen-high-hopes-11th-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart |archivedate=January 23, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5877859/pitbull-kehas-timber-still-tops-hot-100-bastille-lorde-reach-top-10 |title=Pitbull & Ke$ha's 'Timber' Still Tops Hot 100; Bastille, Lorde Reach Top 10 |first=Gary |last=Trust |work=Billboard |date=January 22, 2014 |accessdate=January 23, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140123081527/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5877859/pitbull-kehas-timber-still-tops-hot-100-bastille-lorde-reach-top-10 |archivedate=January 23, 2014 }}</ref> The following week, February 8, the song still remains atop the Hot Digital Song adding another 294,000 units to the number of copies sold during the previous weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5885814/grammy-awards-generate-sales-gains-on-billboard-charts |title=GRAMMY Awards Generates Sales Gains On Billboard Charts |first=Keith |last=Caulfield |work=Billboard |date=January 29, 2014 |accessdate=January 29, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131084040/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5885814/grammy-awards-generate-sales-gains-on-billboard-charts |archivedate=January 31, 2014 }}</ref> On January 29, 2014, \"Dark Horse\" reached the number one position in the United States, giving Perry her ninth US number one and tying her with four other artists as the artist with the tenth highest number ones in history, and also becoming Juicy J's first number one US hit.  Perry also set a new record, becoming the only artist to have a number one single in each year of the decade thus far.<ref name=\"NumberOneBillboard\">{{cite web|last=Trust |first=Gary |title=Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Gallops to No. 1 on Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5885830/katy-perry-dark-horse-hot-100-no-1 |work=Billboard |accessdate=January 29, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131082410/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5885830/katy-perry-dark-horse-hot-100-no-1 |archivedate=January 31, 2014 }}</ref>  The song topped the chart for four straight weeks, from February 8 to March 1. It was replaced by [[Pharrell Williams]]' \"[[Happy (Pharrell Williams song)|Happy]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Pharrell Williams' 'Happy' Hits No. 1 On Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5915783/pharrell-williams-happy-hits-no-1-on-hot-100 |publisher=NielsenSoundscan |author=Trust, Gary |accessdate=February 26, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228104221/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5915783/pharrell-williams-happy-hits-no-1-on-hot-100 |archivedate=February 28, 2014 }}</ref> The song also broke Perry's record for her longest stay within the top 10 for one single - as \"Dark Horse\" spent 22 weeks within the top ten, breaking her previous record set by \"[[E.T. (song)|E.T.]]\" of 20 weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6106532/iggy-azalea-hot-100-fancy-magic-calvin-harris |work=Billboard |title=Iggy Azalea Remains Atop Hot 100 With 'Fancy'; MAGIC!, Calvin Harris Hit Top 10 |first=Gary |last=Trust |date=2014-06-04 |accessdate=2014-06-04 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606210505/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6106532/iggy-azalea-hot-100-fancy-magic-calvin-harris |archivedate=June 6, 2014 }}</ref> The song has spent 52 weeks on the Hot 100 as of September 18, 2014, becoming Perry's first song to last at least a year on the chart.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry - Chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/305595/Katy+Perry/chart?f=793 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=September 24, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629090241/http://www.billboard.com/artist/305595/Katy%20Perry/chart?f=793 |archivedate=June 29, 2014 }}</ref> By May 2014, \"Dark Horse\" has sold over 5 million copies in the US, and become Perry's 6th song to surpass the 5 million mark.<ref name=\"Dark Horse Digital Sales 2014\">{{cite news|title=Chart Watch: MJ Makes Hot 100 History |url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-mj-makes-hot-100-history-225547952.html |author=Paul Grein |publisher=Yahoo! |date=May 21, 2014 |accessdate=May 22, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140522043849/https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-mj-makes-hot-100-history-225547952.html |archivedate=May 22, 2014 }}</ref> It became the third best-selling song of 2014 in the United States with 4.43 million copies sold for the year.<ref name=\"us sales 2014\">{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/music/its-official-pharrell-has-2014s-best-selling-106748836876.html |title=It's Official: Pharrell Has 2014's Best-Selling Song |author=Paul Grein |date=December 31, 2014 |publisher=Yahoo! Music |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401070235/https://www.yahoo.com/music/its-official-pharrell-has-2014s-best-selling-106748836876.html |archivedate=April 1, 2015 }}</ref> As of February 2017, the song has sold 6.3 million copies in the nation,<ref name=USsales>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7694308/ask-billboard-katy-perrys-career-song-album-sales |title=Ask Billboard: Katy Perry's Career Song & Album Sales |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=February 20, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222052835/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7694308/ask-billboard-katy-perrys-career-song-album-sales |archivedate=February 22, 2017 }}</ref> and been certified 11\u00d7 Platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA). The single has sold more than 17 million worldwide as of June 2018.<ref name=RIAA/>\n\nAside from topping the Hot 100, \"Dark Horse\" has also topped [[Mainstream Top 40|Pop Songs]], giving Perry her 11th number-one. This feat tied her with [[Rihanna]] for most number ones on [[Mainstream Top 40|Pop Songs]] chart. \"Dark Horse\" has also topped the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] thus becoming her 13th number one and breaking her own record for most consecutive number ones. Her earlier record which was established upon her second single \"[[Unconditionally (song)|Unconditionally]]\" topping the chart was 12 consecutive number ones.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5901178/chart-highlights-u2-makes-history-on-alternative-songs-with |title=Chart Highlights: U2 Makes History On Alternative Songs With 'Invisible' |first=Gary |last=Trust |work=Billboard |date=February 10, 2014 |accessdate=February 11, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302012154/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5901178/chart-highlights-u2-makes-history-on-alternative-songs-with |archivedate=March 2, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nIn Canada, the song has reached the top-spot position, becoming the singer's tenth number-one single in the country and Juicy J's first.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry - Chart history |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/305595/Katy+Perry/chart?f=793 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=January 9, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140629090241/http://www.billboard.com/artist/305595/Katy%20Perry/chart?f=793 |archivedate=June 29, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===Oceania and Europe===\nOn the week-ending September 23, 2013, \"Dark Horse\" debuted at number ten on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]] becoming Perry's twelfth top ten.<ref name=\"nzchart2\">{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2273 |title=NZ Chart: Week of September 23, 2013 |work=Charts.org.nz |publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=September 27, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103151034/http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2355 |archivedate=January 3, 2014 }}</ref> Five weeks later, the song peaked at number two, and charted in the top 10 for a total of 16 weeks. It has gone on to receive double platinum certification, and spent 37 weeks in the top 40.<ref>{{cite web|title=KATY PERRY FEAT. JUICY J - DARK HORSE (SONG)|url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Katy+Perry+feat%2E+Juicy+J&titel=Dark+Horse&cat=s|work=charts.nz|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=January 27, 2014}}</ref>\nIn Australia, the song was not eligible to chart on the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Top 100 Singles Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/pharrell-williams-vs-inxs-on-next-chart-midweek-sales-20140312 |title=Pharrell Williams Vs INXS On Next Chart MIDWEEK SALES |publisher=Noise11 |last=Ryan |first=Gavin |date=March 12, 2014 |accessdate=August 13, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409010031/http://www.noise11.com/news/pharrell-williams-vs-inxs-on-next-chart-midweek-sales-20140312 |archivedate=April 9, 2014 }}</ref>{{why|date=August 2018}} but peaked at number five on the ARIA Top 50 Digital Tracks.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20131024-0000/issue1232.pdf|title=ARIA Report: Week Commencing 7 October 2013|date=October 24, 2013|publisher=[[Pandora Archive]]|issue=1232|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn the UK, on September 22, 2013, \"Dark Horse\" debuted at number 21 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"UKSinglesChart\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2013-09-28 |title=2013 Top 40 Official Singles Chart UK Archive: 28th September 2013 |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |accessdate=September 25, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926184927/http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/1/2013-09-28 |archivedate=September 26, 2013 }}</ref> It re-entered the chart at number 19 on February 2, 2014. Four weeks later, it reached a new peak of number 4. On January 23, 2014 the song re-entered the [[Irish Singles Chart]] at number 47<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2014&year=2014&week=4 |title=Irish Singles Chart |accessdate=February 26, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219051837/http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2014&year=2014&week=4 |archivedate=February 19, 2014 }}</ref> then reached a peak of 3.{{citation needed|date=September 2014}}\n\nOn the week-ending October 10, 2013 the song entered the [[Single Top 100|Dutch Mega Top 100]] chart at number 74, when \"Dark Horse\" was just a promotional song from the album. More than three months later, when the song was released as the third official single, \"Dark Horse\" re-entered the chart at number 28. Six weeks later, the song topped the chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Katy+Perry+feat%2E+Juicy+J&titel=Dark+Horse&cat=s|title=Dutch Mega Top 100|accessdate=February 26, 2014}}</ref> The song also reached the top spot position on the [[Dutch Top 40]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.top40.nl/top40/2014/week-8 |title=Dutch Top 40 |accessdate=February 26, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225221552/http://www.top40.nl/top40/2014/week-8 |archivedate=February 25, 2014 }}</ref>\nIn Austria, the Czech Republic, Norway and Sweden, the song peaked at number 2. \"Dark Horse\" also managed to reach the top 10 in Finland and Denmark where it respectively peaked at number 5 and 6. \"Dark Horse\" topped the Belgian Ultratop 50 Flandre chart and reached the top 10 in other European countries such as France and Germany.{{citation needed|date=September 2014}}\nIn Italy, on the week-ending March 13, 2014, the song entered the [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]] official top 20 at number 17 and, after five weeks, it has so far reached a peak of number 5. It has also been certified gold for sales of 15,000 copies.{{citation needed|date=September 2014}}\n\n==Music video==\n===Background and production===\nIn an interview with ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' at the [[56th Annual Grammy Awards|2014 Grammy Awards]], Juicy J stated the video will be filmed \"soon\"; he added that it is \"a major motion picture.\" He further teased the release by saying, \"I can't really tell you because it's definitely going to be a surprise, but I'll tell you this much right here: you've seen her other videos, this one's gonna be just as big. Everything she does is like grade A.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Juicy J Talks 'Dark Horse' Collaboration, Potential New Album |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/grammys-2014/5885494/juicy-j-talks-dark-horse-collaboration-and-video-potential-new |work=Billboard |accessdate=January 28, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131071033/http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/grammys-2014/5885494/juicy-j-talks-dark-horse-collaboration-and-video-potential-new |archivedate=January 31, 2014}}</ref>\n\nWhen \"Dark Horse\" had attained the top position on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100 Chart, Perry announced that she was working on the video. \"<ref name=\"NumberOneBillboard\" /> On February 6, 2014, Perry tweeted the video would be released \"soon\".<ref>{{cite tweet|user=katyperry|number=431317371798552576|author=Katy Perry|date=February 6, 2014|title=Ermagherd derk herse holds steady for the 2nd week @ #1! THANK YEW! Would you like a video? Okee! Hold yer herses...SOON!}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/katyperry/view/103748/?isworld=y |title=Katy Perry promises video \"soon\" as 'Dark Horse' stays at No.1 in US |work=Press Party |date=February 6, 2014 |accessdate=July 7, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708070706/http://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/katyperry/view/103748/?isworld=y |archivedate=July 8, 2015 }}</ref> On February 13, 2014, she released a preview of the music video onto her [[Vevo]] account on [[YouTube]], revealing the Egyptian setting of the video. Perry played a character named \"Katy P\u00e4tra\", a takeoff on the [[Egyptians|Egyptian]] queen [[Cleopatra]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry \u2013 Dark Horse (Music Video Preview) |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwqiKh1twTM |publisher=YouTube |date=February 13, 2014 |last=Perry |first=Katy |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161205134517/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwqiKh1twTM |archivedate=December 5, 2016 }}</ref> The video was released on February 20, 2014.<ref name=\"VidRelease\">{{cite news|last=Montgomery |first=James |title=Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Video Premieres: Watch It Now |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1722651/katy-perry-dark-horse-video/ |publisher=MTV News |accessdate=February 20, 2014 |date=February 20, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707001539/http://www.mtv.com/news/1722651/katy-perry-dark-horse-video/ |archivedate=July 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe music video was directed by [[Mathew Cullen]], who previously worked with Perry on her music video for the song \"[[California Gurls]]\". Perry's idea for the music video was to combine Ancient Egyptian culture with Memphis, Tennessee [[hip hop]]: setting the video in ancient [[Memphis, Egypt]] as a nod to Juicy J's Tennessee hometown. Speaking of Perry's concept, Cullen said \"That's music to my ears \u2014 when an artist has a couple concepts that they want to mash up to create something fresh.\"<ref name=\"TimeMagazine\">{{cite journal|last=Rothman |first=Lily |title=Katy Perry Dark Horse Music Video: Egypt Setting Gets OK from Experts |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2014/02/21/katy-perry-dark-horse-egypt/ |journal=Time |accessdate=February 24, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223223043/http://entertainment.time.com/2014/02/21/katy-perry-dark-horse-egypt/ |archivedate=February 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Synopsis===\n[[File:Dark Horse Disintegration.png|thumb|right|The video was criticized for including a scene where Perry's character disintegrated a man (pictured), originally seen wearing a pendant appearing to display the [[Arabic language|Arabic]] word for \"[[Allah]]\", which was subsequently edited out of the video]]\nDuring the video's opening, it is revealed that the music video takes place \"a crazy long time ago\" in [[Memphis, Egypt]]. For the opening verses, Perry's character Katy P\u00e4tra, the witch of Memphis, is shown wearing a white dress and white and blue wig while floating on a large [[barge]] at sunset, with pyramids and palm trees visible in the background. The video transitions to a different scene where P\u00e4tra, now wearing a longer dress and a black wig, sits in an extravagant [[Sphinx]]-like throne while pharaohs gather to bring her expensive gifts (such as a large [[diamond]]) in an attempt to \"win her heart.\"\n\nAfter retrieving the first suitor's gift, she hits the man with a magical bolt of lightning from her hand, turning him into a pile of sand, and takes his jewels to wear on her teeth as a [[grill (jewelry)|grill]]. Another suitor brings her [[candy]], [[cupcake]]s, [[twinkie]]s, and spicy [[cheese puffs]]. After she burns her mouth with the spicy cheese puffs, she turns the suitor into a large cup of water, which she drinks. P\u00e4tra also appears as a gray statue in a scene where golden pythons and gray guardian statues such as [[Anubis]], [[Horus]], [[Nisroch]] and [[Apep]] surround her, and in a scene with a blue background where she wears a golden dress and several golden hieroglyphs levitate around her.\n\nDuring Juicy J's verse, the rapper emerges from a gold [[sarcophagus]] while P\u00e4tra accepts an Egyptian chariot with hydraulics (she turns the associated suitor into a set of giant dice to hang from the frame) and rejects a suitor who turns out to have the [[Sobek|face of a crocodile]] by turning him into a wallet. During the final chorus, the last suitor brings P\u00e4tra a large gold pyramid with a pink capstone, which she ascends. At the top of the pyramid, P\u00e4tra, dressed as [[Isis]], uses her powers to conjure up a magical \"perfect storm\" with pink, purple, and violet clouds. Although it seems like P\u00e4tra has finally found a gift she likes, the final frame of the video reveals that she has turned the final suitor into a [[Japanese urban legend#Jinmenken (\"Human-Faced Dog\")|dog with a human head]].\n\n===Reception===\nThe music video was criticized by some for appropriating the symbols and imagery of Egyptian culture. Cullen, the director, defended the music video, saying that, while he believes it is dangerous to rip things directly from present cultures without adding anything to them, Ancient Egypt is part of what he calls our \"shared collective mythology\". He said: \"The most important thing is that when you create something, and this is actually something Katy and I worked to do \u2014 you bring a new spin to it.\" Egyptologist [[David P. Silverman]] praised the music video's use of Egyptian imagery and the interest it could generate to viewers: \"[Egypt has] always been a part of popular culture. It encourages people to think of these things, and some of those people actually begin to learn a lot.\" The video was noted by conspiracy theorists for bearing resemblance to imagery used by the alleged [[Illuminati]], but Ritner rejected the allegations, saying that \"The many discussions of the Illuminati are nonsense\" and that, in fact, the [[Freemasonry|masonic]] imagery associated with the Illuminati is drawn from Egyptian imagery (as a common source for both).<ref name=\"TimeMagazine\" />\n\nOn June 9, 2015, the music video for \"Dark Horse\" became the first video by a female artist to reach 1 billion views on [[Vevo]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Passes 1 Billion Vevo Views |first=Erin |last=Strecker |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6590902/katy-perry-dark-horse-1-billion-vevo-views |journal=Billboard |date=June 10, 2015 |accessdate=June 10, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612233806/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6590902/katy-perry-dark-horse-1-billion-vevo-views |archivedate=June 12, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry Just Beat Taylor Swift To A Huge Milestone |first=Gil |last=Kaufman |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2181184/katy-perry-dark-horse-billion-video-taylor-swift/ |publisher=MTV News |date=June 9, 2015 |accessdate=June 9, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610090021/http://www.mtv.com/news/2181184/katy-perry-dark-horse-billion-video-taylor-swift/ |archivedate=June 10, 2015}}</ref> Perry also became the first female to have a video on [[YouTube]] with 1 billion views.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/music/news/a31487/katy-perry-just-left-taylor-swift-in-the-dust-on-youtube/ |title=Katy Perry Just Left Taylor Swift in the Dust on YouTube |magazine=[[Seventeen (American magazine)]] |accessdate=August 1, 2015 |date=June 9, 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723153039/http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/music/news/a31487/katy-perry-just-left-taylor-swift-in-the-dust-on-youtube/ |archivedate=July 23, 2015}}</ref> As of March 2020, the video has received over 2.7 billion views on YouTube, making it the [[List of most viewed YouTube videos#All-time|18th most viewed video of all time]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Top 1000 Most Viewed YouTube Videos of All Time|url=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL11E57E1166929B60 |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=March 8, 2020 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809182529/https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLirAqAtl_h2r5g8xGajEwdXd3x1sZh8hC |archivedate=August 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Accusations of blasphemy====\nThe music video caused controversy among some [[Muslim]]s who criticized a scene in the video where a man wearing a [[pendant]] appearing to display the [[Arabic]] word for \"[[Allah]]\" is disintegrated and turned into sand by Perry's character. The scene took place 1 minute and 15 seconds into the video. A petition launched on [[Change.org]] accused Perry of \"representing an opposition of God\" and demanded that the video be taken down from [[YouTube]]. The petition reached over 65,000 signatures and as a response, the pendant was digitally removed from the video on February 26, 2014, after which the petition was closed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry Dark Horse video edited |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-26366249 |work=BBC News |accessdate=February 27, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227124602/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-26366249 |archivedate=February 27, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Copyright infringement lawsuit==\n\nOn July 1, 2014, the ''[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]'' reported that Christian rapper [[Flame (rapper)|Flame]] and others filed a lawsuit against Perry, Capitol Records, and Perry's co-writers for infringing copyright on the song \"Joyful Noise\", which appeared on the 2008 album ''[[Our World: Redeemed]]''.<ref name=\"post-dispatch\">{{cite web|last1=Patrick |first1=Robert |title=St. Louis Christian hip-hop singers sue Katy Perry over 'Dark Horse' |url=https://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/st-louis-christian-hip-hop-singers-sue-katy-perry-over/article_a18ee60f-8f8d-5e5e-bdb1-cbfaff93597d.html |website=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]] |accessdate=July 3, 2014 |date=July 1, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820073736/http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/st-louis-christian-hip-hop-singers-sue-katy-perry-over/article_a18ee60f-8f8d-5e5e-bdb1-cbfaff93597d.html |archivedate=August 20, 2014 }}</ref> The producer, Chike Ojukwu, along with co-songwriter [[Da' T.R.U.T.H.]] were listed as co-plaintiffs.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/7eef738596e9458eacb9f9015d7fd7fe|title=Jury: Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' copied Christian rap song|last=Andrew Dalton|date=July 30, 2019|website=AP NEWS|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/legal-and-management/8524466/katy-perry-dark-horse-guilty-verdict-dr-luke-max|title=Katy Perry Loses 'Dark Horse' Copyright Trial|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=July 29, 2019|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref> Cho'zyn Boy, a DJ for Flame in 2014, stated that Perry's song is \"identical\" to \"Joyful Noise\", but ten BPM slower in tempo and one step higher in pitch.<ref name=\"rapzilla\">{{cite web|last1=Daniels |first1=David |title=Flame's DJ Explains Why 'Joyful Noise' and Katy Perry's 'Dark Horse' Are Similar |url=http://www.rapzilla.com/rz/news/38-backstage/8695-flames-dj-explains-why-joyful-noise-and-katy-perrys-dark-horse-are-similar |website=[[Rapzilla]] |publisher=Philip Rood and Chad Horton |accessdate=July 3, 2014 |date=July 2, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140706182725/http://www.rapzilla.com/rz/news/38-backstage/8695-flames-dj-explains-why-joyful-noise-and-katy-perrys-dark-horse-are-similar |archivedate=July 6, 2014 }}</ref> In addition to the infringement claims, the suit claimed that \"by any measure, the devoutly religious message of 'Joyful Noise' has been irreparably tarnished by its association with the witchcraft, paganism, black magic, and Illuminati imagery evoked by the same music in 'Dark Horse'\".<ref name=\"huffpo\">{{cite news|last1=Sieczkowski |first1=Cavan |title=Christian Singers Sue Katy Perry Over 'Dark Horse' |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/07/02/christian-singers-sue-katy-perry-dark-horse-_n_5552496.html |work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=July 3, 2014 |date=July 2, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703011143/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/07/02/christian-singers-sue-katy-perry-dark-horse-_n_5552496.html |archivedate=July 3, 2014 }}</ref> Rapper [[Lecrae]], who is featured on the song was and was initially included as a plaintiff in the lawsuit, clarified to MTV that \"I was in Hong Kong [when] the press release went out and it's not my song \u2014 it's my guy Flame's song and I respect everyone's intellectual properties \u2014 but that statement about the witchcraft and stuff, that's not my statement and I don't stand behind that statement.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nadeska |first1=Alexis |title=Is Lecrae Really Involved In A Katy Perry Lawsuit? Not So Fast |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1876925/lecrae-responds-katy-perry-lawsuit/ |publisher=[[MTV News]] |accessdate=July 25, 2014 |date=July 23, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140726202025/http://www.mtv.com/news/1876925/lecrae-responds-katy-perry-lawsuit/ |archivedate=July 26, 2014 }}</ref> To divest himself from the lawsuit, Lecrae signed over his rights to the song to Flame, Da' T.R.U.T.H., and Ojukwu for free.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8522201/katy-perry-dark-horse-trial-musicologist-backs-up-copyright-claim|title=Musicologist Backs Up Copyright Infringement Claim Against Katy Perry on Day Two of 'Dark Horse' Trial|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=July 20, 2019|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, [[Christina A. Snyder]] from the [[United States District Court for the Central District of California]] ruled against a [[summary judgment]], arguing that the plaintiffs \"demonstrated a triable issue of fact as to access because 'Joyful Noise' achieved critical success, including a Grammy nomination, and was readily available and viewed millions of times on YouTube and MySpace.\"<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/katy-perry-dr-luke-facing-copyright-trial-dark-horse-1135670|title=Katy Perry, Dr. Luke Facing Copyright Trial Over \"Dark Horse\"|last=Gardner|first=Eriq|date=August 17, 2018|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref> She also deferred to the arguments of musicologist [[Todd Decker]], who claimed that the songs share \"five or six points of similarity\"; specifically, the [[Ostinato|ostinatos]] in both songs are either identical or nearly so in their [[Phrase (music)|phrase length]], rhythm, [[Pitch (music)|pitch content]], and [[timbre]].<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> Perry and Dr. Luke countered with their own expert testimony from musicologist Lawrence Ferrara that the commonalities between the two songs are merely [[Genre|generic]] elements.<ref name=\":2\" /> During the federal trial in July 2019, Perry, Dr. Luke, and Max Martin testified that they had never heard \"Joyful Noise\", and that of the trillions of videos uploaded to YouTube between 2009 and 2013, and their defense team attempted to demonstrate that \"Joyful Noise\" was not widely accessible to audiences.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/29/arts/music/katy-perry-dark-horse-copyright.html|title=Katy Perry Loses Copyright Battle Over 'Dark Horse'|last=Sisario|first=Ben|date=July 29, 2019|newspaper=The New York Times|accessdate=July 30, 2019}}</ref> The lawyer for Flame and the other plaintiffs noted that Perry in the early 2000s started her career in [[Contemporary Christian music|Christian pop]], to which Perry replied that even during that part of her career she was \"mostly always listening to ... secular music anyway\".<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":5\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8521289/katy-perry-takes-stand-dark-horse-copyright-trial|title=Katy Perry Takes the Stand on Day One of 'Dark Horse' Copyright Trial|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=July 19, 2019|magazine=Billboard|access-date=July 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFerrara argued that \"Dark Horse\" contains elements common to countless songs, including the much older songs \"[[Mary Had a Little Lamb]]\", \"[[Jolly Old Saint Nicholas|Jolly Old St. Nicholas]]\", and \"[[Merrily We Roll Along (song)|Merrily We Roll Along]]\".<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> Decker claimed that the descending melodies of each ostinato are unique and that he had not \"seen another piece that descends in the way these two do.\"<ref name=\":4\" /> The attorney for Perry and fellow defendants accused Flame and the other plaintiffs of \"trying to own basic building blocks of music, the alphabet of music that should be available to everyone.\"<ref name=\":1\" /> Another argument from Perry and the other defendants was that because Ojukwu never registered the beat he produced and later licensed it to Flame, \"Joyful Noise\" was itself a derivative work.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> When Perry testified before the court, initially technical difficulties prevented her lawyers from playing \"Dark Horse\" in the courtroom, and Perry joked \"I could perform it for you live.\"<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> On July 29, 2019, a federal jury found that Perry, Juicy J, Dr. Luke, Max Martin, Cirkut, and Sarah Hudson were guilty of infringement, along with Capitol Records, Warner Bros. Music Publishing, Kobalt Publishing, and Kasz Money Inc.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> The jury awarded the plaintiffs $2.78 million, of which Perry herself was ordered to pay $550,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/katy-perry-dark-horse-lawsuit-payment-1.5233968|title=Katy Perry among those ordered to pay a total of $2.78M in song copying lawsuit|last=|first=|date=August 1, 2019|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|access-date=August 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\nPerry and the other defendants appealed the ruling to Judge Snyder.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://news.bloomberglaw.com/ip-law/katy-perry-appeals-2-8-million-dark-horse-copyright-verdict |title= Katy Perry Appeals $2.8 Million 'Dark Horse' Copyright Verdict |first = Kyle | last= Jahner | date = October 18, 2019 | accessdate = March 17, 2020 | work = [[Bloomberg Law]] }}</ref> While the appeal was under consideration, in early March 2020, the [[United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit|Ninth Circuit]] (of which the Central District of California is a part of) issued a ruling in a similar long-running lawsuit on whether [[Led Zeppelin]]'s \"[[Stairway to Heaven]]\" violated the copyright of the song \"[[Taurus (instrumental)|Taurus]]\" from the band [[Spirit (band)|Spirit]]. In its ruling, the Ninth found that \"Stairway\" did not violate the copyright of \"Taurus\", specifically overturning its \"[[inverse ratio rule]]\" which it had used in several previous cases.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://variety.com/2020/music/news/led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-copyright-lawsuit-1203527581/ | title = Led Zeppelin Scores Big Win in 'Stairway to Heaven' Copyright Case | first=  Gene | last = Maddaus | date = March 9, 2020 | accessdate = March 9, 2020 | work = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] }}</ref> Perry's lawyers took this ruling as part of their appeal to Judge Snyder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.law360.com/media/articles/1253762/katy-perry-says-stairway-ruling-crushes-dark-horse-verdict|title=Katy Perry Says 'Stairway' Ruling Crushes 'Dark Horse' Verdict|date=March 16, 2020|accessdate=March 17, 2020|work=Law360}}</ref> On March 17, 2020, Judge Snyder overturned the jury award, citing numerous factors, including that the evidence given did not support the jury's award, and of the recent Ninth Circuit judgement. Snyder wrote \"A relatively common 8-note combination of unprotected elements that happens to be played in a timbre common to a particular genre of music cannot be so original as to warrant copyright protection\". Snyder vacated the jury's verdict and denied motions for a new trial, though stated that should the case be heard on appeal at the Ninth Circuit, that a new jury trial would be required.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://variety.com/2020/music/news/katy-perry-dark-horse-reversal-1203537482/ | title = Katy Perry Wins Reversal of 'Dark Horse' Copyright Verdict | first= Gene | last= Maddaus | date = March 17, 2020 | accessdate = March 17, 2020 | work = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Katy Perry and Capitol Records win appeal in \u2018Dark Horse\u2019 copyright case |url=https://musicbiznation.com/news/katy-perry-wins-appeal-dark-horse-case/ |publisher=Music Biz Nation}}</ref><ref>[https://www.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.cacd.624044/gov.uscourts.cacd.624044.525.0.pdf]</ref>\n\n== Live performances ==\n[[File:Katy Perry - The Prismatic (Newark) 06.jpg|thumb|175px|right|Perry performing \"Dark Horse\" at [[The Prismatic World Tour]]]]\n\"Dark Horse\" was first performed at the [[iHeartRadio Music Festival]] in [[Las Vegas]] on September 20, 2013.<ref name=\"MTV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1714419/katy-perry-iheart-radio.jhtml |title=Katy Perry Brings The Hits And Juicy J! To iHeartRadio Music Festival |publisher=MTV News |accessdate=September 25, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130924000908/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1714419/katy-perry-iheart-radio.jhtml |archivedate=September 24, 2013 }}</ref> It was later performed at the [[iTunes Festival]] in London.<ref name=\"Katy debuts Walking on Air in London\">{{cite web |url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/music/news/katy-perry-closes-itunes-festival-29622275.html?|title=Katy Perry closes iTunes Festival |work=The Belfast Telegraph |accessdate=October 1, 2013}}</ref> Perry also performed the song with Juicy J at the We Can Survive event at the [[Hollywood Bowl]] on October 23.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globalgrind.com/2013/10/24/katy-perry-juicy-j-dark-horse-performance-video-we-can-survive-charity-concert/ |accessdate=February 16, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222141534/http://globalgrind.com/2013/10/24/katy-perry-juicy-j-dark-horse-performance-video-we-can-survive-charity-concert/|title=GET IT GIRL! Watch Katy Perry Body Roll For Juicy J (VIDEO) |archivedate=February 22, 2014 }}</ref> Perry also performed \"Dark Horse\" on ''[[The Voice of Germany]]'' on December 13, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.directlyrics.com/watch-katy-perry-performs-dark-horse-unconditionally-on-the-voice-of-germany-news.html |title=Katy Perry Performs 'Dark Horse' & 'Unconditionally' on 'The Voice of Germany' |publisher=directlyrics.com |date=December 14, 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219091947/http://www.directlyrics.com/watch-katy-perry-performs-dark-horse-unconditionally-on-the-voice-of-germany-news.html |archivedate=December 19, 2013 }}</ref> Perry and Juicy J performed the song at the [[56th Annual Grammy Awards]] on January 26, 2014. The \"dark and mysterious\" performance featured a \"haunted forest\" design with [[animatronic]] horses, broomstick pole dances, and a controlled fire.<ref name=\"GrammyPerformance2014\">{{cite web|last=Rogulewski |first=Charley |title=Katy Perry And Juicy J Perform 'Dark Horse' At 2014 Grammys |url=http://www.vibe.com/article/watch-katy-perry-and-juicy-j-perform-dark-horse-2014-grammys |work=Vibe |date=January 26, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140129021850/http://www.vibe.com/article/watch-katy-perry-and-juicy-j-perform-dark-horse-2014-grammys |archivedate=January 29, 2014 }}</ref> The singer also performed the song at the [[2014 BRIT Awards]] and the performance featured a neon-colored Egyptian theme, like the music video.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee |first=Ashley |title=Katy Perry Goes Egyptian Neon for 'Dark Horse' At BRIT Awards: Watch |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5908538/katy-perry-goes-egyptian-neon-for-dark-horse-at-brit-awards-watch |publisher=Nielsen |date=February 19, 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301230104/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5908538/katy-perry-goes-egyptian-neon-for-dark-horse-at-brit-awards-watch |archivedate=March 1, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nOn February 1, 2015, the song was performed by Perry during the [[Super Bowl XLIX halftime show]], where she was on a chessboard, with her dancers as chess pieces. It was one of the most technical performance out of the rest of the performances.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lipshutz |first1=Jason |title=Katy Perry Shines During Super Bowl XLIX Halftime Show |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/super-bowl-2015/6458199/katy-perry-super-bowl-xlix-halftime-show-review |accessdate=February 1, 2015 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |agency=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=February 1, 2015 |location=United States |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203202853/http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/super-bowl-2015/6458199/katy-perry-super-bowl-xlix-halftime-show-review |archivedate=February 3, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from ''Prism'' album liner notes.<ref name=\"Notes 2\">{{cite AV media notes|title=Prism|titlelink=Prism (Katy Perry album)|others=[[Katy Perry]]|year=2013|type=liner notes|publisher=[[Capitol Records]]|location=United States}}</ref>\n\n*[[Katy Perry]] \u2013 lead vocals, backing vocals, songwriter\n*[[Juicy J]] \u2013 featured vocals, backing vocals, songwriter\n*[[Sarah Hudson (singer)|Sarah Hudson]] \u2013 songwriter\n*[[Dr. Luke]] \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*[[Max Martin]] \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*[[Cirkut (record producer)|Cirkut]] \u2013 producer, songwriter\n\n==Formats and track listings==\n*'''Digital download'''<ref name=\"iTunes\" />\n#\"Dark Horse\" \u2013 3:35\n\n*'''Digital download \u2013 Japan version'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/jp/album/dark-horse-feat.-tee-single/id830272318 |title=iTunes - \u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af - \u30b1\u30a4\u30c6\u30a3\u30fb\u30da\u30ea\u30fc\u300cDark Horse