atical Practitioners: Benjamin Banneker|place=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[National Museum of American History|Smithsonian Institution Museum of History and Technology]]|year=1964|pages=22\u201325|lccn=64062352|oclc=999972|accessdate=2017-10-07|journal=United States National Museum Bulletin|number=231|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Bedini|first=Silvio A.|url=http://www.boundarystones.org/articles/rchs_1969.pdf |format=pdf |title=Benjamin Banneker and the Survey of the District of Columbia, 1791|journal=Records of the [[Historical Society of Washington, D.C.|Columbia Historical Society]]|volume=69/70|pages=7\u201330 |year=1969|jstor=40067703|oclc=3860814|accessdate=2013-01-13|via=[http://www.boundarystones.org boundarystones.org]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007223056/http://www.boundarystones.org/articles/rchs_1969.pdf|archivedate=2017-10-07}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bedini|first=Silvio A.|year=1972|url=https://archive.org/details/lifeofbenjaminba00silv/page/n8/mode/1up|title=The Life of Benjamin Banneker|place=New York|publisher=[[Charles Scribner's Sons|Scribner]]. Republished by Landmark Enterprises, [[Rancho Cordova, California]], 1984.|isbn=0910845204|oclc=593414330|lccn=78162755|accessdate=August 29, 2019|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Bedini|first=Silvio A.|jstor=40072968|title=The Survey of the Federal Territory: Andrew Ellicott and Benjamin Banneker|journal=Washington History|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=[[Historical Society of Washington, D.C.]]|volume=3|date=Spring\u2013Summer 1991|number=1|pages=76\u201395}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bedini|first=Silvio A.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WIMYAAAAIAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22Banneker%2C+Benjamin%22|editor1-last=Salzman|editor1-first=Jack|editor2-first=David Lionel|editor2-last=Smith|editor3-first=Cornel|editor3-last=West|title=Banneker, Benjamin|work=Encyclopedia of African-American Culture and History|edition=1st|volume=1: Aar-Cit|year=1996a|p